This paper discusses the computational complexity of finding approximate Nash equilibria, which is a problem in computational complexity theory and game theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper also involves algorithms and optimization, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the use of calibration algorithms, which could fall under cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
